OL,3,CFootball teams finally play Cold War-
OL,4,Cdelayed fixture
OL,6,FA football match that should have
OL,7,Fkicked-off 65 years ago has finally
OL,8,Fbeen completed.
OL,10,FIt was a game scrapped because of the
OL,11,FCold War, but now Glenavon and German
OL,12,Fside Erzgebirge Aue have fulfilled
OL,13,Ftheir European Cup tie.
OL,15,FThe story of this game dates back to
OL,16,Fthe 1960-61 season.
OL,18,FGlenavon, as Irish League Champions,
OL,19,Fand the East German league winners,
OL,20,Fthen known as Wismut, were due to face-
OL,21,Foff in a European clash.
